This article summarizes remarks made by President Trump during a meeting with members of the African American community. The President discussed various topics, including law enforcement, education, business, and health. He also mentioned his plans to resume his political rallies, starting with one in Tulsa, Oklahoma, and mentioned the possibility of moving the Republican Convention to another location due to issues with the governor of North Carolina. The President and his supporters highlighted his administration's achievements, such as criminal justice reform, opportunity zones, and support for historically black colleges and universities. They also discussed the need for police reform and increased access to capital for the black community.